16:38.786 --> 16:43.153
All right, here's the next thing this fall, and that is, you know, we had a great summer of first Wednesdays.

16:43.173 --> 16:44.995
I wanna bring this back to the surface.

16:45.015 --> 16:46.538
Maybe you were traveling a lot and miss those.

16:46.978 --> 16:49.342
First Wednesdays is an important part of church life.

16:49.903 --> 17:01.260
This year we have really, and even moving forward, we have focused on Galatians chapter four that says, this is the Apostle Paul saying this, he says, my dear children, for whom I'm again in the pains of childbirth until Christ is forming you.

17:01.541 --> 17:05.947
He's expressing his passion for the fullness of God to be formed on the inside of us.

17:05.987 --> 17:07.730
Not just a little taste of God,

17:08.418 --> 17:13.765
But all of God, not just living on milk, but living on solid food spiritually.

17:13.785 --> 17:16.368
And that's what first Wednesdays are all about.

17:16.448 --> 17:18.411
And so it's really all about faith formation.

17:18.871 --> 17:23.797
And we actually have first Wednesday this week, and we've targeted a specific area that is so important.

17:23.817 --> 17:24.999
And that's the area of finances.

17:25.059 --> 17:27.682
And we have Dave Ramsey, who was with us earlier this year.

17:27.722 --> 17:28.423
He's back with us.

17:28.443 --> 17:29.264
Yeah, come on, Uncle Dave.

17:29.284 --> 17:30.206
I love Uncle Dave.

17:30.826 --> 17:36.914
And so he is locked and loaded to help us in a very spiritual area, the area of finances.

17:37.378 --> 17:43.366
to bring orders to that area, and I'm super excited about that, and all of our fall first Wednesdays.

17:43.386 --> 17:49.593
And here's the last kind of road map, and you've already heard this one, I won't stay here long, but we are officially launching our fall small groups today.

17:49.653 --> 17:55.461
And as a church, we are called to community, to commune with God and with each other.

17:55.981 --> 17:59.786
And I am so excited that we're launching those groups to last for the next 13 weeks.

18:00.207 --> 18:01.709
What a great chance to go online today.

18:01.769 --> 18:06.034
All those groups are listed where they meet the day, the time, the topic,

18:06.274 --> 18:07.596
And you may even have to try out a few.

18:08.477 --> 18:09.338
That's completely okay.

18:09.358 --> 18:10.900
Your leaders are ready for rejection.

18:10.960 --> 18:14.504
The leaders that are there, if you go from their group to the next one, we have prepared their hearts.

18:14.544 --> 18:15.265
It's not about that.

18:15.305 --> 18:16.566
It's about you finding the right group.

18:16.967 --> 18:17.788
That's what it's all about.

18:18.309 --> 18:21.512
And so please know that that's our passion and kind of the rally cry.

18:21.532 --> 18:24.556
You're gonna hear it a lot from me all fall along is together we win.

18:25.357 --> 18:26.118
And that's the truth.

18:26.138 --> 18:27.199
We need each other more.

18:27.279 --> 18:30.523
We need God and we need each other more than ever before.

18:30.623 --> 18:31.945
And so that's kind of fall programming.

18:32.526 --> 18:36.050
And I'm really excited that along with that, kind of built up to this moment,

18:36.354 --> 18:43.883
that we're putting a fresh vision focus on an area of our church and in the state of Alabama that is so important.

18:44.304 --> 18:48.769
We launched down in Montgomery around 15 years ago in our capital city of Montgomery.

18:49.290 --> 18:53.495
And we have an amazing campus there that's been led by Pastor Chris Irwin, his wife Rachel.

18:53.555 --> 19:00.603
God has used that campus for 15 years for people to know God and find freedom, discover purpose, and to make a difference.

19:00.663 --> 19:06.130
And God really just led us as a church to bring back focus to that area in a huge way.

19:06.210 --> 19:14.320
The first way we're gonna do that is we were actually beginning construction on the Montgomery Dream Center this fall, which I'm so, yeah, put your hands together, it's exciting.

19:16.282 --> 19:19.206
Which is a hub of outreach, obviously, for us.

19:19.226 --> 19:24.813
We were able just to show, as I said earlier, it was served a, show city of Montgomery the love of Jesus.

19:25.553 --> 19:31.140
And it's an important city with a military base there and with colleges there and just the families that live in that community.

19:31.741 --> 19:35.986
Also, just being our capital city here in Alabama, for us just to show the love of Jesus,

19:36.130 --> 19:40.297
in moments and services, but also practically with those red shirts on.

19:40.397 --> 19:42.019
And it's such an incredible opportunity.

19:42.580 --> 19:43.562
It is fully funded.

19:43.602 --> 19:46.426
I wanted to celebrate that by the generous people of Church of the Highlands.

19:46.927 --> 19:51.514
And so we're able just to build that debt free and that facility is gonna start in the next month or so.

19:51.915 --> 19:57.183
And then along with that, again, a focus to that area, I'm officially announcing, I kinda teased it at Team Knight.

19:57.203 --> 19:58.586
The dot was actually up there earlier.

19:58.646 --> 20:03.954
I mentioned that earlier when we showed you the whole state or the whole campus church map.

20:04.098 --> 20:09.384
But we are announcing today the launch of the Prattville campus in February 26th.

20:09.725 --> 20:11.607
Church of the Highlands has come into Prattville.

20:12.168 --> 20:19.416
Pratt Vegas is going to be awesome, which just now gives us two locations in that region to God be the glory.

20:19.536 --> 20:23.301
It's going to be an incredible opportunity to reach that entire region with a dream center, two campuses.

20:23.862 --> 20:28.547
And honestly, guys, this was so easy because we really already have a campus in Prattville.

20:29.268 --> 20:30.930
Because for the last five years,

20:31.202 --> 20:33.024
They have been meeting for 21 days.

20:33.244 --> 20:34.966
I mean, small groups, outreach.

20:35.006 --> 20:36.268
That's kind of like a black market small group.

20:36.288 --> 20:39.291
They basically forced us to turn that into a, or a black market campus.

20:39.532 --> 20:41.174
They forced us to turn that into a campus.

20:41.574 --> 20:42.275
And I am so excited.

20:42.295 --> 20:43.737
I even have family members in Prattville.

20:43.757 --> 20:44.738
I know they're so excited.

20:45.238 --> 20:51.566
And I believe with all of my heart, for decades to come, God is gonna use that campus to make a difference.

20:51.586 --> 20:55.711
And I know we're not physically in that space, but one more time all across church life.

20:55.731 --> 20:58.674
Can we welcome the people of Prattville

20:59.970 --> 21:00.631
We love you.

21:00.651 --> 21:01.552
We're so excited.

21:03.234 --> 21:10.364
And before I share a little bit on just vision for our own lives, we put together a video just to give you a little more of God's picture of what's happening in the city of Montgomery.

21:10.404 --> 21:10.865
Check it out.

21:13.728 --> 21:17.974
I can remember 15, 16 years ago when we were praying about this area.

21:18.635 --> 21:23.141
I remember meeting with Pastor Chris and saying, I'd love to bring highlands to Montgomery.

21:23.341 --> 21:25.784
And Pastor Chris said, well, we'd love to be in Montgomery.

21:25.804 --> 21:27.026
We knew then

21:27.490 --> 21:30.714
that God wanted to do something really, really special in this area.

21:33.879 --> 21:37.303
We have seen so many people healed and set free.

21:37.543 --> 21:38.665
They have found their purpose.

21:38.725 --> 21:39.706
They're part of the team.

21:40.327 --> 21:46.515
And now the local church right here in the central part of our state has not only grown, but it's thrived.

21:49.519 --> 21:54.546
We're so thankful that God has given us so many opportunities to do lots of outreach in this area.

21:54.626 --> 21:56.869
And we've always loved this vision of dream centers.

21:57.130 --> 21:58.952
We have one in Birmingham, one in Auburn.

21:59.032 --> 22:02.237
We love that that was Pastor Chris's vision and Hart, now Pastor Marks.

22:02.978 --> 22:05.462
And now Montgomery is now getting their own.

22:06.564 --> 22:13.954
We're excited because there's so much opportunity to meet needs and minister to people and to mobilize more team.

22:16.198 --> 22:18.481
How do we share the love of Jesus?

22:18.902 --> 22:21.946
How do we become the church between Sundays?

22:22.527 --> 22:24.530
And that is the mission of the dream center.

22:26.370 --> 22:32.236
One of the greatest things that we love is being in the community so much, we've been doing outreach here for 20 years.

22:32.897 --> 22:39.824
And to watch life change happen, not just in the building, but in the community, has been incredible.

22:40.645 --> 22:46.291
When you think about this area, this area does include a few cities, and one of those being Prattville, Alabama.

22:50.435 --> 22:53.458
We've heard for years, can we get our own campus?

22:53.538 --> 22:55.840
It's a community that we've actively been serving.

22:56.220 --> 22:58.943
It's a community that is full of highlands families.

22:59.183 --> 23:02.606
You just see the growth of families, the amount of schools in our area.

23:02.986 --> 23:08.931
People are, you know, flocking to this area between military, you know, going to both the bases and whatnot.

23:09.292 --> 23:15.357
When you look at where is the natural next place for us to go, it's where we already have so many great church family.

23:15.517 --> 23:19.801
And we've seen them drive in, you know, 40 minutes to be with us on Sunday.

23:20.081 --> 23:23.524
And that's why we've done so many small groups and outreach there.

23:23.504 --> 23:29.032
It introduced us to people who were trying to live life just like we were.

23:29.052 --> 23:37.785
That really helped us to surrender our issues and problem to God and just let Him just work it out.

23:37.805 --> 23:40.049
We realize now, okay, it's time to do more.

23:40.710 --> 23:42.512
That we need a Sunday experience.

23:42.532 --> 23:43.914
We need a campus life.

23:43.934 --> 23:46.418
We need a campus family in Bratville, Alabama.

23:47.970 --> 24:04.752
We want really to dive our family a lot deeper into ministry, into just loving on people and community and have our children grow up seeing that and living that and having a campus that's in our city, the impact that that's going to make on their lives and the community is going to be great.

24:05.493 --> 24:10.419
To just be able to see the light of Jesus spread to so many other places.

24:10.639 --> 24:12.722
We're excited for all God's about to do.

24:12.898 --> 24:14.561
The opportunity has never been greater.

24:15.061 --> 24:16.584
We have the resources we need.

24:16.644 --> 24:21.150
We have the amazing dream team to reach a city that is hurting, that is broken.

24:21.311 --> 24:22.072
We're not leaning back.

24:22.132 --> 24:24.776
We are doubling down on the capital city.

24:25.096 --> 24:29.663
And as one church, this is exciting for all of us, not just Montgomery and not just Brabble.

24:29.683 --> 24:32.648
Now new family members will come into our church.

24:33.068 --> 24:33.990
They will become us.

24:34.450 --> 24:42.162
We will become the family of God and we'll do great things together, maybe in a different zip code, but in the same family, the body of Christ.

24:44.034 --> 24:45.135
Yeah, come on, somebody.

24:45.275 --> 24:46.837
What an incredible opportunity.

24:46.877 --> 24:53.123
And again, Bravo, we officially welcome you as we begin to launch that campus all fall on the first day in February.

24:53.143 --> 24:54.484
It's going to be a day to celebrate.

24:54.604 --> 24:57.307
And Psalm 115, one is on my heart today.

24:57.327 --> 25:02.092
I just want to finish kind of the vision for our church section with this, not to us, Lord, not to us, but to your name.

25:02.612 --> 25:05.475
Be the glory because of your love and faithfulness.

25:05.495 --> 25:07.938
And the church said, amen, amen.

25:07.978 --> 25:12.402
So I want to take these last few moments and minister to you.

25:12.962 --> 25:17.508
If you would even open your heart, as we talk about vision for the church, I wanna talk about vision for our own lives.

25:17.528 --> 25:20.052
We wanna have God's perspective for the future of our church.

25:20.833 --> 25:24.558
But I've been praying for God's perspective, what he sees over all of our own lives.

25:25.159 --> 25:28.544
And I have had so many conversations recently, I know it's not an accident.

25:29.205 --> 25:38.418
In fact, I think this will be a series in 2026 because there's been just conversation with young people, highlands college and other places about how do I find vision for my life

25:38.498 --> 25:41.041
You know, what does that look like, my next step after college?

25:41.061 --> 25:49.352
I've talked to a lot of people my own age, which I have to admit now, like in those middle-aged years, I'm middle-aged in those mid-40s, like, what does my second half look like in the next decade and a half?

25:49.372 --> 25:50.714
What does God have for me?

25:51.314 --> 25:56.761
And then just even people who are older in our church, full of wisdom, and like, how do I take all that God's done in my life?

25:57.242 --> 26:00.726
And what is the vision for these next years as I invest that into other people?

26:00.786 --> 26:06.674
And time after time when I've had those discussions, and I don't know if this is everybody, but I know because of those and other

26:06.914 --> 26:13.823
discussions, it's a lot of us, that there's a temptation or a tendency at least, for that to come along with some weight.

26:14.985 --> 26:29.725
I think vision is exciting, can be very exciting, but oftentimes, when we talk about vision for our own lives, we can feel like we somehow missed it, or the pressure of figuring it out can be so overwhelming, it can just feel literally like a weight sitting on our shoulders.

26:29.745 --> 26:36.594
And I talk to a lot of people, that's even how they describe it, they're almost paralyzed with like the what next or the how I get from here to what God wants.

26:36.674 --> 26:37.295
from my life.

26:37.355 --> 26:40.640
It can come with fear, confusion, guilt, and just a lot of anxiety.

26:40.700 --> 26:42.442
And again, it's person after person.

26:42.462 --> 26:43.444
I know it's no accident.

26:43.484 --> 26:45.787
And so I'm even going to pray for us right now.

26:45.807 --> 26:48.231
I even have the keys out just for this to be more of a heart moment.

26:48.832 --> 26:54.580
I mean, I want to just share for the next eight or nine minutes a message I know is from heaven for all of us.

26:54.680 --> 27:01.670
And again, there's more even in the practical sense for this calling or vision idea, but I know God wants to lift the way today.

27:02.772 --> 27:04.274
If you'll allow them, Jesus, thank you.

27:04.578 --> 27:06.020
for your presence is so faithful.

27:06.260 --> 27:07.061
You are here right now.

27:07.822 --> 27:09.365
God, thank you for the vision of this house.

27:09.425 --> 27:10.346
We are so confident.

27:10.366 --> 27:16.434
There's things in front of us, but God, just as that's true for our church, it is true for every life in the sound of my voice.

27:17.195 --> 27:19.879
So enemy, get your hands off of them, their minds, their hearts.

27:20.219 --> 27:21.641
God, I'm praying for the way to be lifted.

27:21.681 --> 27:27.529
And we, to have your eyes, your perspective, your ability, God to focus on what really matters as it relates to vision.

27:27.549 --> 27:30.153
God, do what only you can in this moment in Jesus' name.

27:30.614 --> 27:33.778
And everybody said, amen, everybody said,

27:33.890 --> 27:34.751
Amen.

27:35.332 --> 27:36.353
Philippians 1, 6.

27:37.054 --> 27:38.476
I preached it earlier about the church.

27:38.516 --> 27:39.397
I want to come back to it.

27:39.958 --> 27:49.049
It's being confident of this that he who began a good work in you will carry it on to what completion?

27:49.650 --> 27:51.592
I want to lean in on those three ideas.

27:51.833 --> 27:55.237
He began it, he carries it, and he will complete it.

27:56.258 --> 28:00.484
He began the work, he carries the work, and he will complete it.

28:01.124 --> 28:02.386
Here's the big idea of

28:02.978 --> 28:03.619
He began it.

28:03.719 --> 28:09.090
Here's really the big idea of vision is that God is the initiator of vision.

28:10.272 --> 28:12.958
At the end of the day, it is not my vision.

28:13.018 --> 28:14.821
That's honestly where we often go wrong.

28:14.842 --> 28:15.904
That's where the weight comes in.

28:16.565 --> 28:17.507
It's not our vision.

28:17.627 --> 28:21.835
It's his vision that God is the author of our story.

28:22.176 --> 28:23.639
Our story didn't begin with us.

28:24.120 --> 28:25.202
It began with him.

28:25.634 --> 28:27.916
Jeremiah 2911, let this minister to you today.

28:28.337 --> 28:39.528
For I know the plans I have for you declares the Lord plans to prosper you and not to harm you, plans to give you hope and a future God has plans and they are good plans and they are His plans.

28:40.709 --> 28:41.510
So how do I find those?

28:41.530 --> 28:43.652
That's kind of the place we find ourselves.

28:43.672 --> 28:44.553
How do I find those plans?

28:44.573 --> 28:45.654
How do I find that vision?

28:46.535 --> 28:47.916
Here's something that's gonna encourage you.

28:47.936 --> 28:51.600
In the Bible, calling is used as both a noun and a verb.

28:52.600 --> 28:54.162
You know, how do I find my calling?

28:54.626 --> 28:56.208
As a noun, it's used four times.

28:56.248 --> 29:00.174
I'll talk about the verb usage in a moment, but as a noun, it's used four times.

29:00.214 --> 29:05.081
Many different instances of a verb, but as a noun, it's used four very intentional times.

29:05.121 --> 29:06.283
One of those is Ephesians 4.

29:06.303 --> 29:11.330
It says, as a prisoner for the Lord, then I urge you to live a life worthy of the calling you have received.

29:11.770 --> 29:19.922
Every single time that calling is used as a noun like this, it is used to talk about our salvation, that our ultimate calling

29:20.482 --> 29:23.467
God's ultimate vision for our life is a relationship with him.

29:23.747 --> 29:24.508
I'll say it this way.

29:24.528 --> 29:28.855
Our ultimate calling is to know him and make him known.

29:29.175 --> 29:33.141
That is the hope and future Jeremiah 29 is talking about in that instance to the people of Israel.

29:33.702 --> 29:39.251
And there in that scripture it is talking about us that we are called to know him and to make him known.

29:39.271 --> 29:42.095
This is why the Bible never tells us to find our calling.

29:42.435 --> 29:44.779
Come on somebody because our calling was never lost.

29:45.901 --> 29:46.802
It's not lost.

29:47.362 --> 29:48.484
It's to know and make him known.

29:48.744 --> 29:55.275
And we can know God and make him known exactly where we are, even if it's not the circumstances that we wish or that we hope for.

29:55.956 --> 29:57.158
We'll talk more about that in a moment.

29:58.120 --> 29:59.442
But, hey, church, you are called.

30:00.223 --> 30:00.804
Where are you called?

30:00.865 --> 30:01.566
Right where you are.

30:01.606 --> 30:04.611
To know God and to make him known.

30:05.092 --> 30:12.284
Today, tomorrow, every person you encounter, the opportunities that are in front of us, they're all a part of our calling.

30:12.985 --> 30:13.746
To know him.

30:14.178 --> 30:14.979
and make him known.

30:15.420 --> 30:17.122
Let that just begin to lift some weight off.

30:17.142 --> 30:22.549
And of course, the verse continues to say that he will also carry those good works on.

30:22.589 --> 30:23.590
He will carry them.

30:24.512 --> 30:25.953
God is the initiator of vision.

30:26.354 --> 30:28.196
The Holy Spirit is the sustainer of vision.

30:28.237 --> 30:29.338
This is good news, everybody.

30:30.219 --> 30:32.963
That God doesn't just throw plans at us and say, good luck.

30:33.704 --> 30:34.945
God is not like IKEA.

30:35.326 --> 30:36.888
I don't know if you're IKEA people out there.

30:37.348 --> 30:41.554
You go to IKEA, you buy the furniture, it's in a box, you bring it home, and you pull the plans out.

30:41.666 --> 30:44.329
And it's like a good luck, because there's no words, it's just pictures.

30:44.409 --> 30:48.935
I have never put together a piece of IKEA furniture the right way the first time.

30:48.975 --> 30:50.377
I'm so grateful that God's not like that.

30:50.397 --> 30:52.440
He's not like, all right, I made you a plan.

30:52.620 --> 30:53.501
Good luck figuring it out.

30:54.182 --> 30:55.403
That God gives us his spirit.

30:55.443 --> 31:04.695
When we know Jesus, when we experience salvation, we are filled with the spirit of God, which prays God for a GPS and all the different maps that we have here on earth.

31:04.735 --> 31:10.162
There is no better director for our life than the power of the Holy Spirit.

31:11.138 --> 31:20.652
Philippians 2, 13, it is God, Holy Spirit is God who works in you to will and act in order to fulfill his good purpose.

31:21.293 --> 31:23.677
When we know God, there's never gonna be a day.

31:23.717 --> 31:28.143
We don't have the sustaining, directing power of the Holy Spirit.

31:28.945 --> 31:31.268
He will lead us into those plans.

31:32.390 --> 31:37.277
He will lead us step by step, calling as a noun, calling in the Bible is also a verb.

31:38.379 --> 31:40.722
And every time calling, old and New Testament is used,

31:40.834 --> 31:43.217
And the verbs tense, check this out.

31:43.298 --> 31:44.299
It just means this.

31:45.140 --> 31:47.644
He invites you to his next assignment for you.

31:48.485 --> 31:50.408
That our entire life, it's not a singular calling.

31:50.428 --> 31:51.750
That's what puts a lot of weight on young people.

31:51.770 --> 31:52.991
It's like, I gotta figure it out.

31:53.692 --> 31:57.358
And some of those older people can tell you, you ain't gonna figure it out at 17 years old.

31:57.878 --> 32:01.924
Cause our life is a journey and the Holy Spirit is faithful to lead us from place to place to place.

32:01.944 --> 32:03.526
Look at the Apostle Paul and others in the Bible.

32:03.847 --> 32:05.750
They were continually being called.

32:06.150 --> 32:07.392
And how do we stay in tune with that?

32:07.772 --> 32:08.914
We stay intimate.

32:08.994 --> 32:14.904
with God, we live a spirit-led life, which is not some mystical life, it just means I am.

32:15.385 --> 32:17.449
I'm gonna always stay close to Him.

32:17.489 --> 32:21.055
It's all about, spirit-led life is all about intimacy with God.

32:21.797 --> 32:23.259
How do we receive that next invitation?

32:23.500 --> 32:24.281
We stay close to Him.

32:24.662 --> 32:25.884
How do we receive that next invitation?

32:25.924 --> 32:26.926
We stay in His Word.

32:27.266 --> 32:29.490
How do we receive that next invitation, that next assignment?

32:29.791 --> 32:31.213
We stay around the people of God.

32:31.734 --> 32:33.938
Come on, this is what Galatians says, Galatians 5,

32:34.018 --> 32:36.642
We live by the spirit, let us keep in step with the spirit.

32:36.662 --> 32:42.190
